sequenceDiagram
    participant browser
    participant server
    
   Note: the browser sends the user input to the server
    browser->> server : POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note
    Note: the server responds to the Post request by asking the server to perform a GET request to another address, specified in the header Location
    server -->> browser : GET /exampleapp/notes
    
    Note: the browser reloads the page
    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/notes
    server-->>browser: HTML document

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.css
    activate server
    server-->>browser: the css file
    deactivate server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.js
    activate server
    server-->>browser: the JavaScript file
    deactivate server

    Note: the JavaScript code is executed and the JSON is fetched from the server

    Note: the HTML form tag's method attribute defines how the form is submitted, while the action attribute defines the address that recieves the request

    browser->> server: POST /exampleapp/new_note

    Note: The server handles the POST request creating a new object for each new note with two properties, date and content, and pushing into an array stored in the JSON file
    Note: the inline HTML written in JavaScript file makes the new notes visible
